race.comment: ALVARINHO (8) impressed when resuming in an easier 1100m race at Hobart last start, scoring comfortably by a length. She is just as sharp second up and will carry the same weight here. A wide gate is against her, but with the right run, she can be very competitive again. DURAZZO (2) settled near the rear before charging home to finish runner-up behind the top pick in the same race when resuming over 1100m. He has won 5 of his 6 starts here, and the extra 100m will make all the difference. Hard to beat. THESPIAN WATERS (7) resumes from a spell and normally comes to hand quickly. He was close up in a recent trial, and with an ounce of luck from a tough gate, he can figure in the top 4. CANNONBALL (1) will be peaking third up after a couple of runs on the mainland, including his last run at Flemington two weeks ago. His trainer would not be here just for the scenery. AND BEYOND (4) worked home late last start at Hobart on soft ground. He is a veteran now but is still capable.
